      <text>
        The orientation chamber was larger than the intake room, its vine-walled surfaces curving into something almost like a classroom. Bioluminescent patches provided steady light, and several vine-formed seats faced a flat presentation surface.

        Scout bounced to one of the seats and settled—an encouraging motion.

        Kira lowered herself down; her leg had moved from throbbing to a steady ache that colored everything. How many hours until the temporary treatment wore off? How much longer until this was over?

        A sound drew her attention—smooth mechanical rolling. A plant entered the chamber on a wheeled platform.

        The platform itself was remarkable: three wheels arranged for stability, built from what looked like salvaged materials yet operating with impressive smoothness. A thick central stem rose, branching into an array of enormous flowers—each bloom easily fifteen centimeters across, pale cream with petals fully open.

        Delicate tendrils extended from the main stem to manipulate a joystick embedded in the platform. The movements were precise, elegant even. The whole setup rolled to the front of the chamber and came to a perfectly controlled stop.

        A voice, careful and refined, came from the flowers—

        "Good evening! I'm Florence. I'll be coordinating your workplace safety orientation today."

        The flowers shifted subtly—petals repositioning, color bleeding toward pale yellow.

        Kira asked, "This is... Florence?"

        Florence replied, "Yes." The flowers deepened slightly to a warmer yellow—"I'm very pleased to assist with your onboarding process. Shall we begin?"

        Scout bounced once—encouragement or approval, hard to say.

        From a fruiting body near the wall, Holloway's voice emerged—

        "Florence has prepared a comprehensive presentation on workplace safety fundamentals. Please give your full attention!"

        ¶

        "Workplace safety."

        Kira had crashed from space. Her ship had exploded. She was stranded on an alien planet. And they were going to teach her workplace safety.

        Florence said, "Let's start with proper lifting techniques." The flowers shifted to a focused cream tone—"This is essential for preventing workplace injuries."

        A series of images appeared on the presentation surface, pressed or grown into bark, showing simplified figures in various lifting postures.

        Florence continued, "When lifting heavy objects, it's crucial to bend at the knees, not the waist. Keep your back straight, core engaged, and lift with your legs."

        Kira stared.

        Kira asked, "What objects am I lifting?"

        Florence answered, "Workplace materials, of course—equipment, supplies, documentation." The flowers flickered briefly orange—was that confusion or concern?—"The principles apply to any lifting scenario."

        Kira said, "I don't have a workplace—I crashed here."

        Buddy interjected helpfully—*"Exactly why this training is so important!"*
